TITLE: Avoiding Signal Writing in Effects with Leptos
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates an anti-pattern where a signal is updated within an effect, which can lead to inefficient update chains and potential infinite loops. The solution is to derive values instead of explicitly updating signals.
SOURCE: https://github.com/leptos-rs/leptos/blob/main/docs/COMMON_BUGS.md#2025-04-18_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
let (a, set_a) = create_signal(0);
let (b, set_b) = create_signal(false);

create_effect(move |_| {
	if a() > 5 {
		set_b(true);
	}
});
```

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
let (a, set_a) = create_signal(0);
let b = move || a () > 5;
```

