TITLE: Using OrPoisoned Trait with RwLock in Rust
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use the OrPoisoned trait to handle potentially poisoned RwLock states. The trait provides a cleaner alternative to using .unwrap() or .expect() when dealing with lock poisoning.
SOURCE: https://github.com/leptos-rs/leptos/blob/main/or_poisoned/README.md#2025-04-18_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
use or_poisoned::OrPoisoned;
use std::sync::RwLock;

let lock = RwLock::new(String::from("Hello!"));

let read = lock.read().or_poisoned();
// this is identical to
let read = lock.read().unwrap();
```

