TITLE: Implementing Basic Reactive System with Signals and Effects in Rust
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the core functionality of the reactive system by creating a signal, a computed value (memo), and an effect. Shows how updating the signal automatically propagates changes through the reactive graph.
SOURCE: https://github.com/leptos-rs/leptos/blob/main/reactive_graph/README.md#2025-04-18_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
use reactive_graph::{
    computed::ArcMemo,
    effect::Effect,
    prelude::{Read, Set},
    signal::ArcRwSignal,
};

let count = ArcRwSignal::new(1);
let double_count = ArcMemo::new({
    let count = count.clone();
    move |_| *count.read() * 2
});

// the effect will run once initially
Effect::new(move |_| {
    println!("double_count = {}", *double_count.read());
});

// updating `count` will propagate changes to the dependencies,
// causing the effect to run again
count.set(2);
```

