TITLE: Demonstrating Oco Smart Pointer Usage in Rust
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to use the Oco smart pointer with different types of string references (static, Arc, and owned). The code demonstrates the smart pointer's ability to handle various string types and its efficient cloning mechanism.
SOURCE: https://github.com/leptos-rs/leptos/blob/main/oco/README.md#2025-04-18_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
use oco_ref::Oco;
use std::sync::Arc;

let static_str = "foo";
let arc_str: Arc<str> = "bar".into();
let owned_str: String = "baz".into();

fn uses_oco(value: impl Into<Oco<'static, str>>) {
    let mut value = value.into();

    // ensures that the value is either a reference, or reference-counted
    // O(n) at worst
    let clone1 = value.clone_inplace();

    // these subsequent clones are O(1)
    let clone2 = value.clone();
    let clone3 = value.clone();
}

uses_oco(static_str);
uses_oco(arc_str);
uses_oco(owned_str);
```

