TITLE: Displaying E2E Testing Directory Structure in Bash
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows the directory structure for organizing end-to-end tests in a Leptos project. It includes feature files, test fixtures, and the main test suite file.
SOURCE: https://github.com/leptos-rs/leptos/blob/main/examples/suspense_tests/e2e/README.md#2025-04-18_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
features
└── {action}_{object}.feature   # Specify test scenarios
tests
├── fixtures
│   ├── action.rs               # Perform a user action (click, type, etc.)
│   ├── check.rs                # Assert what a user can see/not see
│   ├── find.rs                 # Query page elements
│   ├── mod.rs
│   └── world
│       ├── action_steps.rs     # Map Gherkin steps to user actions
│       ├── check_steps.rs      # Map Gherkin steps to user expectations
│       └── mod.rs
└── app_suite.rs                # Test main 
```

